                                            <div style="text-align: justify">
                                                <p>
                                                    DCL is the foremost governing body for cricket leagues in DFW area. As of 2017, it represents 115 teams and clubs! DCL administrates the game and works with enrolled league members in each season throough its proven and popular league framework. DCL governance
                                                    includes schedules for enrolled teams, face-off opponents, distribution of grounds evenly and managing local preferences of league members if they have home grounds. DCL assigns custodians and match
                                                    umpires that officiate at all sanctioned league matches and tournaments to maintain high standards including game records. DCL presides over the League Code of Conduct, Playing Conditions as per Policies
                                                    by Cities, the Ethical Issues, Grievance Reviews, Constitution and Bylaws.



                                                    <br/>
                                                    <br/> We promote cricket by delivering exciting and engaging events, tournaments, attracting new and diverse fans and building long-term successful city-community partnerships. And finally, we will continue
                                                    to make considerable efforts to protect the integrity of the sport. As of now, DCL governs cricket in 15+ cities as per field use agreements or through profoundly aligned cricket associations.

                                                </p>

                                                <p>
                                                    DCL has constituted carefully programs, focus groups and robust mechanisms to manage league, tournaments and its operations:
                                                    <ul>
                                                        <li><b>Youth Center of Excellence</b> to develop and execute programs that attracts youth, promote talent and grow cricket at grass roots level.</li>
                                                        <li><b>Office of Envisioning</b> to develop the future strategy, outlook and set direction including digitalization and experience excellence.</li>
                                                        <li><b>Ethical Committee</b> that leads with long-term philosophical approach and responsibility programs such as "Leave No Trace".</li>
                                                        <li><b>Cricket Evangelism CoE</b> to expand cricket and new grounds in DFW. It includes relationships with the city officials and local communities.</li>
                                                        <li><b>Umpiring Committee</b> that conducts seminars to train and certify umpires to raise qaulity of league games organized by DCL.</li>
                                                        <li><b>Scheduling Committee</b> that works relentlessly to plan thousands of games annually e.g. league seasons, corporate tournaments, intercity events etc.</li>
                                                        <li><b>Discipline Committee</b> that manages issues related to fairness, safety, code of conduct and grievances.</li>
                                                        <li><b>League Custodians</b> as a focus group to ensure reliable digital records for teams, players and scorecards.</li>
                                                        <li><b>Awards and Recognition Panel</b> that organize DCL Award Events (multiple times per year) to celebrate champions, winners, volunteers, contributors and city officials.</li>
                                                        <li><b>Information and Technology Group</b> that focus on DCL apps, modules, websites and 3rd party integration such as Chauka for live experience.</li>
                                                    </ul>
                                                </p>
